            <title><![CDATA[U.S. and Iran truce tested over the Strait of Hormuz, threatening to reignite conflict]]></title>
            <link>https://www.pbs.org/newshour/show/u-s-and-iran-truce-tested-over-the-strait-of-hormuz-threatening-to-reignite-conflict</link>
            <description><![CDATA[The tenuous truce between the U.S. and Iran was tested Monday, as American ships clearing a lane in the Strait of Hormuz came under fire and sank Iranian boats. Iran also fired drones and missiles at a key oil terminal in the United Arab Emirates, spooking markets and raising concerns that war could resume. Nick Schifrin reports. 
